      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BARNAVARA (2) Group 1 Irish-bred mare making her Australian debut for the Waller yard. Was a courageous winner of the G1 Prix De L'Opera at Longchamp last October. Hasn't trialled publicly but looks well placed over her pet trip. Adept in all conditions and expected to go close. BOIS D'ARGENT (1) game first-up second in the G3 Parramatta Cup over 1900m, then faded late with the 58.5kg to run fifth over 2000m in the LR Randwick City Stakes. Not as much pressure here and can play a leading role. WOOTTON VERNI (3) raced much closer to the speed with a disappointing fifth over this journey in the G3 Sky High Stakes at this track. At his top now and the soft conditions enhance his chances. CAVIAR HEIGHTS (6) William Haggas-trained gelding who looks up to this class with a string of minor placings in Listed grade. Maps to tag the speed and respect first-up. STAR OF INDIA (4) capable on his day and going better than his three runs back suggest. Will need a firmer deck to show his best.",
